defaultAnnexdefaultCodentify®default defaultIn 2011 the four major tobacco companies
default 
defaultfounded the 
defaultDigital Coding and Tracking Association (DCTA) with the aim to promote cost effective industry standards and supporting technology solutions to tackle illicit trade. The 
defaultCodentify® 
defaulttechnological solution can deliver product authentication, tracking and tracing and digital tax verification. 
defaultCodentify® product authentication enables law enforcement and other officials to distinguish between genuine and counterfeit products. The system uses unique alphanumeric codes so there will be no need for dedicated scanning devices or specialist training.
default  Codentify is in the process of being rolled out across the UK, with full implementation expected in late 2014/early 2015. 
defaultC
defaultodentify® track and trace will enable stakeholders to monitor and secure the distribution of products worldwide. A unique code is securely applied directly onto every packaging unit.
defaultAs products move along the supply chain between different trading partners, the unique codes are scanned, creating a complete record of its journey history.
defaultThese unique codes, together with Codentify® track and trace data exchange and reporting formats, are based on international standards. This enables all stakeholders throughout the supply chain to use standard equipment and processes to track and trace product movements within and across national borders.
defaultCodentify® track and trace enables law enforcement authorities to retrieve information about the product, its manufacture, distribution and legal status, including products in transit. 
defaultCodentify® track and trace provides law enforcement authorities with the visibility needed to accurately identify national and international illicit trade patterns and assist criminal investigations.
defaultCodentify® digital tax verification enables governments to protect tax revenues by strengthening recovery capabilities and reducing opportunities for evasion.
defaultLicensed manufacturers apply to government for permission to produce online via a secure internet connection. On approval, production can begin under real-time government control. A unique, secure code is applied onto every packaging unit. Once printed, these codes are counted and encrypted production information is immediately and securely communicated to government. Using this information enables governments to accurately calculate and reconcile due taxes. 
defaultCodentify® track and trace will enable stakeholders to monitor and secure the distribution of products worldwide and is fully compliant with the provisions contained in the FCTC Anti-illicit Trade Protocol.
